# Layout (`shared/shell` + `shared/ui`)

## App shell (`shared/shell/`)

Single layout for guest + user + admin portals — **no sidebar**, **no footer**.

- `AppShellComponent` (`app-shell`) — `app-topbar` + scrollable `.app-shell__content` + `<router-outlet>`
- Host class `portal-user` | `portal-admin` from `AuthService.portalKind()` (accent tokens)
- Content padding: `styles/_shell-content.scss` mixin; breakpoint via `styles/_breakpoints.scss`

Registered in `app.routes.ts` as parent of all routes (guest pages + lazy portal trees).

## App topbar (`shared/shell/app-topbar/`)

Modes from `AuthService` + optional `PORTAL_CONFIG`:

| Mode | Left zone | Right zone |
|------|-----------|------------|
| **guest** | Brand; Register always; Sign in link when not on `/` | theme → language |
| **user** | Brand → `homeUrl`; **topbar nav** links from `PortalConfig.topbarNav` (Search, Offer) | theme → language → notifications → account |
| **admin** | Brand → `homeUrl` | theme → language → account |

- `ThemePickerComponent` / `LanguagePickerComponent` — `shared/ui/`; single-click toggles
- `BrandMarkComponent` — optional portal suffix from `PortalConfig.shell.brandSuffixKey`
- Account menu: profile (stub), settings (admin → `ADMIN_SETTINGS_URL`), logout → `SIGN_IN_URL`
- Styles: `styles/_topbar.scss` (`topbar-base`, `topbar-icon-btn`)

## Portal config & topbar nav

- `PORTAL_CONFIG` provided on lazy portal branches in `app.routes.ts` (`USER_PORTAL_CONFIG`, `ADMIN_PORTAL_CONFIG`)
- `PortalConfig.topbarNav: TopbarNavItem[]` — `{ labelKey, route, exact? }`
- User: `portal/user/user-topbar-nav.config.ts` (Search → `USER_FIND_URL`, Offer → `USER_OFFER_URL`)
- Admin: `topbarNav: []` (in-page nav in Plan 3)

## Shared UI widgets (`shared/ui/`)

- `MetricCardComponent` — dashboard KPI tile; parent wraps in `routerLink` when clickable
- `QuickActionCardComponent` — action tile; optional `entityTab` on user portal — see `entity-service-colors.mdc`
- `IntentCardComponent` — intent picker; Home journey + Offer — see `entity-service-colors.mdc`
- `PageTitleComponent` — portal `h1` + subtitle + icon; hubs use `.page-hub-header` — see `page-title.mdc`
- `PageBackLinkComponent` — above title on portal create/edit forms — see `page-title.mdc`
- `RouteDisplayComponent`, `VehicleDisplayComponent`, `DateRangeDisplayComponent`, `WarehouseDisplayComponent`, `StatusBadgeComponent` — table cells; see `tables.mdc`
- `DatePeriodPickerComponent` — filter + form date input — see `forms.mdc`, `table-filters.mdc`
- `PageHeaderComponent` + `PrimaryActionLinkComponent` — list page create CTA — see `page-title.mdc`
- **User hub header:** `.page-hub-header` (`styles/_page-hub-header.scss`) — Find / Our listings — see `entity-tabs.mdc`

## Styling

- Use `@use 'styles/breakpoints' as *` + `@include below-md` in layout SCSS
- **Mobile breakpoint:** `shared/constants/viewport.ts` — `MOBILE_MEDIA_QUERY` (`max-width: 768px`); used by `DataTableComponent`, `FormStepperComponent`
- **Theme surfaces:** 4-layer stack — see `theme-tokens.mdc`. Topbar = chrome; page canvas = `--bg-app`
- **Portal accent:** `AppShellComponent` host `portal-user` | `portal-admin`; tokens in `src/styles/_portal-accent.scss`. Topbar nav active link uses `--portal-accent-muted`. **Do not use `--portal-accent` on portal page content** for links/buttons/cards; guest auth cards may use accent for portal picker CTAs.

